1 (5) the beekeeper's annual gross sales from honey and honeycombs
2 does not exceed $50,000; and
3 (6) the beekeeper harvesting and selling the honey or honeycombs
4 maintains a record of sales of such products. The record shall be available
5 to the Kansas department of agriculture when requested. The record of
6 sales shall include, but not be limited to:
7 (A) The amount of honey or honeycombs sold by container size;
8 (B) where such honey or honeycombs were sold; and
9 (C) the date of such sales.
10 (c) This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the Kansas
11 food, drug and cosmetic act.
12 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 65-689 is hereby amended to read as follows: 65-689.
13 (a) It shall be unlawful for any person to engage in the business of
14 conducting a food establishment or food processing plant unless such
15 person shall have in effect a valid license therefor issued by the secretary.
16 (b) Applications for such licenses shall be made on forms prescribed
17 by the secretary, and each such application shall be accompanied by an
18 application fee and by a license fee. Prior to the issuance of any such
19 license, the secretary shall inspect or cause to be inspected the food
20 establishment or food processing plant designated in the application, to
21 determine that it complies with rules and regulations adopted pursuant to
22 the food, drug and cosmetic act, and amendments thereto. If the food
23 establishment or food processing plant is found to be in compliance, and
24 the completed application and accompanying fees have been submitted,
25 the secretary shall issue the license. If the food establishment or food
26 processing plant is found not to be in compliance, the secretary shall deny
27 the application for a license after providing notice and opportunity for a
28 hearing in accordance with the provisions of the Kansas administrative
29 procedure act.
30 (c) Every license issued hereunder shall be displayed conspicuously
31 in the food establishment or food processing plant for which it is issued,
32 and no such license shall be transferable to any other person or location.
33 Whenever any such license is lost, destroyed or mutilated, a duplicate
34 license shall be issued to any otherwise qualified licensee upon application
35 therefor and the payment of a fee in the amount of $5.
36 (d) A license shall not be required by for:
37 (1) A plant or facility registered or licensed by the department of
38 agriculture pursuant to article 7 of chapter 65 of the Kansas Statutes
39 Annotated, and amendments thereto, or licensed or registered by the
40 department of agriculture pursuant to article 6a of chapter 65 of the Kansas
41 Statutes Annotated, and amendments thereto, shall not be required to
42 obtain a separate license pursuant to this section if the inspections
43 conducted under the respective acts encompass all operations of the

