1 facility.
2 (2) A registered nonprofit organization that provides food without
3 charge solely to people who are food insecure, including, but not limited
4 to, soup kitchens and food pantries.
5 (3) A location where prepackaged individual meals are distributed to
6 persons eligible under the federal older Americans act.
7 (4) A person who produces food for distribution directly to the end
8 consumer, if such food does not require time and temperature control for
9 safety or specialized processing, as determined by the secretary.
10 (5) A person who serves food exclusively on interstate conveyances
11 or common carriers.
12 (6) A person operating a food establishment for less than seven days
13 in any calendar year.
14 (7) A person who prepares, serves or sells food for the sole purpose
15 of soliciting funds to be used for community or humanitarian purposes or
16 educational or youth activities.
17 (8) A person operating a food vending machine, if the food vending
18 machine company:
19 (A) Is licensed as a food establishment, or if located in another state,
20 licensed according to the laws of such state;
21 (B) maintains, and makes available to the secretary, a current record
22 of the location of each food vending machine it operates or services; and
23 (C) conspicuously displays the company name, phone number and
24 any additional information the secretary may require on each such vending
25 machine.
26 (9) A person providing only complimentary coffee to its patrons
27 whose primary business is unrelated to operating a food establishment or
28 food processing plant.
29 (10) A person operating a farm winery, as defined in K.S.A. 41-102,
30 and amendments thereto, who does not produce or offer any food products
31 other than wine produced at such farm winery.
32 (11) A retailer, as defined in K.S.A. 41-102, and amendments thereto,
33 that sells only alcoholic liquors and cereal malt beverages.
34 (12) A food establishment that sells or offers for sale only packaged
35 foods that are non-hazardous and are received directly from a licensed
36 food production facility in packaged form, if such food establishment
37 contains less than 200 cubic feet as measured pursuant to K.S.A. 65-
38 688(e), and amendments thereto.
39 (13) A person who provides food samples, without charge, to
40 promote, advertise or compliment the sale of food or associated food
41 preparation equipment.
42 (14) A guest house, as defined in K.S.A. 36-501, and amendments
43 thereto.

