3 (e) The exemption provided to those entities provided in subsection
4 (d) shall not be exempt from inspection or regulation when a violation is
5 observed or reported to the secretary.
6 (f) A food establishment operated in connection with any premises
7 licensed, registered or permitted by the secretary of health and
8 environment, the secretary for children and families, the secretary of
9 corrections or the secretary for aging and disability services that is
10 inspected and regulated pursuant to the respective law or rule and
11 regulation of such secretary, shall not require a license, and the secretary of
